---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../../../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../../../components/Footer.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Fear | Reading Notes | Clawd ML Portfolio">
  <Nav />
  <main class="reading-note-shell">
    <section class="reading-note-cover" aria-label="Reading note cover image">
      <img
        src={base + "images/atmosphere/reading-notes-cover-hq.webp"}
        alt="A dark film still with a face lit from below and subtitle text about living without fear."
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
      />
    </section>

    <article class="reading-note-body">
      <a class="back-link" href={base + "blog/essays/"}>Back to Field Notes</a>
      <p class="note-label">Reading Notes</p>
      <h1>Fear</h1>
      <section class="note-section">
        <p class="section-kicker">1. Fear arises from duality / separation</p>
        <h2>Bṛhadāraṇyaka Upaniṣad 1.4.2</h2>
        <p class="source-line">Śukla Yajurveda tradition</p>

        <blockquote class="sanskrit-block" lang="sa">
          <p>
            सोऽबिभेत् तस्मादेकाकी बिभेति ।<br />
            स हायमीक्षां चक्रे यन्मदन्यन्नास्ति कस्मान्नु बिभेमीति ।<br />
            तत एवास्य भयं वीयाय ।<br />
            कस्माद्ध्यभेष्यत् । द्वितीयाद्वै भयं भवति ॥
          </p>
        </blockquote>

        <div class="note-translation">
          <p class="translation-label">Transliteration</p>
          <p>so’bibhet tasmād ekākī bibheti… dvitīyād vai bhayaṃ bhavati.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="note-translation">
          <p class="translation-label">Meaning</p>
          <p>
            “He was afraid; therefore one who is alone is afraid. Then he reflected: ‘Since there is nothing other than
            me, what should I fear?’ Then his fear vanished. For what was there to fear? Fear indeed arises from a
            second.”
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="note-section">
        <p class="section-kicker">2. Fearlessness through self-restraint</p>
        <h2>Mahābhārata 12.213.4–5</h2>
        <p class="source-line">Śānti Parva, Mokṣadharma Parva</p>

        <p class="verse-label">Verse 4</p>
        <blockquote class="sanskrit-block" lang="sa">
          <p>
            दमस्तेजो वर्धयति पवित्रं दम उच्यते ।<br />
            विपाप्मा निर्भयो दान्तः पुरुषो विन्दते महत् ॥ ४ ॥
          </p>
        </blockquote>

        <div class="note-translation">
          <p class="translation-label">IAST</p>
          <p>
            damaḥ tejo vardhayati pavitraṃ dama ucyate |<br />
            vipāpmā nirbhayo dāntaḥ puruṣo vindate mahat || 4 ||
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="note-translation">
          <p class="translation-label">Meaning</p>
          <p>
            “Self-restraint increases one’s energy; self-restraint is said to be purifying. The self-restrained person,
            free from sin and fearless, attains greatness.”
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .reading-note-shell {
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .reading-note-cover {
    position: relative;
    width: 100dvw;
    max-width: 100dvw;
    height: clamp(22rem, 58vw, 46rem);
    margin-left: calc(50% - 50dvw);
    overflow: hidden;
    background: rgb(var(--color-ink));
  }

  .reading-note-cover::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      linear-gradient(to top, rgb(var(--color-ink) / 0.82), transparent 44%),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgb(var(--color-ink) / 0.24), transparent 44%, rgb(var(--color-ink) / 0.34));
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  :global([data-theme="bright"]) .reading-note-cover::after {
    background: linear-gradient(to top, rgb(2 6 23 / 0.42), transparent 28%);
  }

  .reading-note-cover img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: none;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: 50% 50%;
    filter: saturate(1.03) contrast(1.04);
  }

  .reading-note-body {
    max-width: 46rem;
    margin: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem) auto 0;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .back-link,
  .note-label {
    color: rgb(var(--color-mist));
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.28em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 180ms ease;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: rgb(var(--color-glass));
  }

  .note-label {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .reading-note-body h1 {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(4rem, 13vw, 8.5rem);
    line-height: 0.86;
    letter-spacing: -0.045em;
  }

  .note-section {
    margin-top: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem);
  }

  .note-section + .note-section {
    border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--color-glass) / 0.12);
    padding-top: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
  }

  .section-kicker,
  .source-line,
  .translation-label,
  .verse-label {
    color: rgb(var(--color-mist));
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .note-section h2 {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    color: rgb(var(--color-glass));
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .source-line {
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
  }

  .verse-label {
    margin-top: 2.25rem;
  }

  .sanskrit-block {
    margin-top: 1.15rem;
    border-left: 1px solid rgb(var(--color-glass) / 0.28);
    padding-left: clamp(1rem, 3vw, 1.5rem);
  }

  .sanskrit-block p {
    color: rgb(var(--color-glass));
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2.3vw, 1.6rem);
    line-height: 2;
  }

  .note-translation {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .note-translation p:last-child {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    color: rgb(var(--color-mist));
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.5vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .reading-note-cover {
      height: 72vw;
      min-height: 18rem;
    }

    .reading-note-body {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
